claim.claim-text:
10. A method of providing imaging for an object using dark field techniques, comprising: 
providing a catadioptric imaging arrangement; 
applying dark field illumination in a predetermined mode and at a predetermined angle to said object; 
forming an intermediate image of said object near an opening, said opening being located on said catadioptric imaging arrangement; and 
resolving said intermediate object image.

32. A method of imaging an object, comprising: 
a) illuminating said object; 
b) collecting light scattered, diffracted or reflected from said object at a plurality of angles; 
c) mapping said collected light to a plane; 
d) selecting at least one imaging mode for analyzing said collected light; and 
e) analyzing said collected light in said imaging mode.

56. An optical system for imaging an object, comprising: 
a) a dome-shaped reflector for collecting light scattered from said object; 
b) a substantially flat reflector which, together with said dome shaped reflector, causes said collected light to pass through an aperture in said dome-shaped reflector; 
c) a means for selecting a portion of said light, which has passed through said aperture, said selected portion corresponding to light scattered over a predetermined range of angles relative to said object, thereby selecting an imaging mode; and 
d) a means for analyzing said portion of said light.

64. A system for imaging an object, comprising: 
a) a dome-shaped reflector positioned above said object, for collecting light scattered from said object over a wide range of angles; 
b) an illumination element for illuminating said object at a variable angle through a portion of said reflector.
